race.comment: CAVERN (9) is a lightly raced 3yo who can take this out. The debut win at Bendigo was very sharp before an even effort when getting back and coming wide at Caulfield Heath, battling away okay for fourth. He should be better for that run and draws much kinder here. EXUBERANCE (7) was just behind AUDIO POP CAM last time out. She gets Craig Williams replacing Ryan Houston here which is noteworthy, especially as he's 1/1 on the horse. TORONADO BOOM (3) ran a good race fresh at Seymour when sticking on for third over 1000m. Better for that and draws well for Stackhouse who can land just off the speed. BALLYNACALLY (6) resumes for her second campaign, now a 5yo mare. She made great strides in her debut campaign and the booking of Linda Meech signals intent for a horse that likes to be up on speed.
